fr.upmc.datacenter.dispatcher

Class RequestDispatcherDynamicState

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.upmc.datacenter.dispatcher.RequestDispatcherDynamicState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataOfferedI.DataI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataRequiredI.DataI, RequestDispatcherDynamicStateI, fr.upmc.datacenter.interfaces.TimeStampingI, java.io.Serializable

    public class RequestDispatcherDynamicState
extends java.lang.Object
implements RequestDispatcherDynamicStateI
    The interface RequestDispatcherDynamicState gives access to the dynamic state information of RequestDispatcher transmitted by data interfaces of RequestDispatcher.

    Description

    The interface is used to type objects pulled from or pushed by a RequestDispatcher using a data interface in pull or push mode. It gives access to dynamic information, that is information subject to changes during the existence of the RequestDispatcher.

    Invariant

     invariant      true

    Cédric Ribeiro et Mokrane Kadri
